latestIgtvVideos.title: Birdhichand and Ishita Mangal present “Bridezilla”
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Jewelry for me means one thing - something that can be passed from one generation to another. Ageless, crafted to perfection and full of emotions. Some of you would know for my brother’s wedding, almost all of us wore @birdhichand jewelry. We have trusted this brand for years and this relationship has only gotten stronger. I love that this luxury jewelry brand has its roots being inspired by the history of India, and I am overjoyed to put together this film for you. 

@birdhichand houses exquisite bridal and fine jewellery at the MI Road, Jaipur & Defence Colony, New Delhi store. @yashagarwal41 

To book your appointments please call on +918585971971 +918585976976.

latestPosts.caption:
Which State Are You From? 🌏
#IshtatesofIndia Finale 🎉

15 August 2023 – 15 June 2024
Over the past 10 months, I’ve embarked on a journey that has tested me in every possible way - emotionally, mentally, and physically. Welcome to #IshtatesofIndia, a series dedicated to celebrating the richness and cultural significance of traditional Indian handlooms from each state and union territory. 🧵✨

Each episode is a vibrant tapestry of handloom, craft, culture, language, drapes, jewelry, patterns, food, and anything unique to the people of the state. The challenge? Serving it up aesthetically and humorously while respecting everyone’s sentiments. Sure, I might have stumbled and made mistakes along the way, but I promise, I did my best to connect with each community and say, “I understand you” in my own way. ❤️

This series was also crafted with the younger generation in mind, who often shy away from investing in handloom traditions due to a lack of awareness. So, if you haven’t already, check out all the episodes in my highlights under #IshtatesofIndia. I really hope you enjoy them and feel the pride of being Indian, no matter where in the world you are. 🌍🇮🇳

A huge shoutout to the hundreds of brands, local people, and, most importantly, my incredible team who helped bring this concept to life. Your support has been amazing. And to my wonderful audience – thank you for your encouragement and engagement. A series like this is driven solely by passion and that energy came from the audience. It was challenging but incredibly fulfilling, all thanks to you! Love you all! 💖

Please share this video with your friends and family! Let’s spread the love and pride! 📣🎥

latestPosts.caption:
Share this hack with a friend who likes natural makeup 😍

#IshtatesofIndia : Kashmir Beauty
In Kashmir, long before lip tints and blushes hit the market, women used the husk of walnuts as natural makeup. When rubbed with water or saliva, the husk leaves behind a soft reddish brown stain that works like a long lasting tint. Rich in natural pigment, this age old beauty hack was not just effective but completely chemical free. A proof that Kashmiri women have always known how to glow, naturally. 

#naturalmakeup #kashmir #kashmir_lovers #traditonal #craft #beautyhack #beautycare

#IshtatesofIndia : Kashmir, Jewelry

Kashmiri jewelry is not just about beauty, it’s about identity, legacy, and resilience. From the sacred Dejhoor to the regal Taranga, every ornament tells a story of tradition and strength. In a land often marked by conflict, these handcrafted pieces carry the silent grace of a culture that refuses to fade.

Outfit: @jogmaya.in 
Pashmina: @hamipashmina 
Jewelry: @akhoonjewellers 

#KashmirKiKahani #TraditionalJewelry #CulturalHeritage #Dejhoor #Taranga #IndianCraftsmanship #JewelsOfIndia

#IshtatesofIndia : Kashmir, Making of Pashmina

Why Support Pashmina?
Because every Pashmina shawl isn’t just a luxury, it’s a lifeline. Behind its softness lies the hard work of Kashmiri artisans who have preserved this centuries-old craft through conflict, climate, and crisis.

Supporting Pashmina means supporting tradition, local livelihoods, and a heritage that deserves to be celebrated, not forgotten.

Pashmina from: @hamipashmina 

#SupportLocalCraft #PashminaLove #HandmadeInIndia #KashmirCraft #SustainableLuxury #CraftWithSoul

#IshtatesofIndia : Kashmir Main Episode

Kashmir has seen more conflict than calm. Behind every beautiful frame, there’s a backstory of unrest, curfews, and resilience. But in the middle of all this, local artisans continue to create beauty like Kashida embroidery, stitch by stitch, thread by thread. Supporting crafts like Kashida isn’t just about fashion, it’s about preserving a culture that refuses to fade even when everything around it tries to.

Kashida Shawl: @hamipashmina 
Suit: @jogmaya.in 
Jewelry: @akhoonjewellers
